<appendix id="quick_install">
  <title>Quick installation guide</title>
  <para>
    This appendix gives a brief overview of the steps that have to be done in
    order to install &ps; on your cluster. A detailed description of the
    necessary steps is contained in <xref linkend="configuration"/> and <xref
      linkend="installation"/>.
  </para>
  <orderedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para><emphasis role="bold">Get the files</emphasis></para>
      <para>
	Get the required files from the <ulink
	  url="http://www.par-tec.com">ParTec homepage</ulink>. You may find
	various versions of &ps; and related software within the <ulink
	  url="http://www.par-tec.com/downloads/download.html">download
	  section</ulink>.
      </para>
<!--      <para>
	Depending on the Linux distribution in use the RPMs or the
	<filename>.tar.gz</filename> files are needed.
      </para>-->
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para><emphasis role="bold">Shutdown</emphasis></para>
      <para>
	If this is actually not the first installation but an update of &ps;
	to a more up to date version first of all shut down the &ps; system.
	In order to do this startup <filename>psiadmin</filename> and do a
	<command>shutdown</command>.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem id="serverinstall">
      <para><emphasis role="bold">Install on the server</emphasis></para>
      <para>
	Install the &ps; distribution files on the server machine.
      </para>
      <para>
	If the <filename>.tar.gz</filename> files are used as installation
	source, <filename>PSM_INSTALL</filename> has to be executed manually.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para><emphasis role="bold">Install on the nodes</emphasis></para>
      <para>
	Depending on the installation model (i.e. centralized or distributed),
	you have to execute <filename>PSM_INSTALL</filename> or to repeat step
	<xref linkend="serverinstall"/> on every node respectively.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para><emphasis role="bold">Configuration</emphasis></para>
      <para>
	Next the configuration file <filename>parastation.conf</filename>
	normally located in <filename>/opt/parastation/config</filename> has to
	be adapted to your local settings.
      </para>
      <para>
	If your installation is a centralized one, this has to be done only on
	the server, otherwise this step has to be repeated on all nodes.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para><emphasis role="bold">Startup &ps;</emphasis></para>
      <para>
	In order to startup the whole &ps; system run
	<xref linkend="psiadmin"/> located in
	<filename>/opt/parastation/bin</filename> and execute
	<command>add</command> at the prompt. This should bring up the &ps;
	daemon <xref linkend="psid"/> on every node. Alternatively you can
	start <xref linkend="psiadmin"/> with the <option>-s</option> option
	which does the add automatically.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para><emphasis role="bold">Testing</emphasis></para>
      <para>
	A brief test of the whole communication system can be done using the
	<filename>test_nodes</filename> program. For a detailed description
	please refer to <xref linkend="testing"/> or to the relevent manual
	page <xref linkend="test_nodes"/>.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </orderedlist>
</appendix>
